    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-05-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Coxe</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States, Guatemala and
                                Honduras</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 105.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to report that the Central American
                    Exposition, the official opening of which occurred on March 15, was thrown open
                    to the public on last Sunday, the 9th instant. It was quite largely attended,
                    the management reporting that 7,000 visitors passed the gates.</p>
                <p>The buildings, grounds, and exhibits present quite an attractive appearance. The
                    exhibits of our citizens, particularly of those of the Pacific slope, are by far
                    the best shown.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macgrane Coxe.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
